3510     def parse_sections(self, offset):
3511         """Fetch the PE file sections. 
3512  
3513         The sections will be readily available in the "sections" attribute. 
3514         Its attributes will contain all the section information plus "data" 
3515         a buffer containing the section's data. 
3516  
3517         The "Characteristics" member will be processed and attributes 
3518         representing the section characteristics (with the 'IMAGE_SCN_' 
3519         string trimmed from the constant's names) will be added to the 
3520         section instance. 
3521  
3522         Refer to the SectionStructure class for additional info. 
3523         """
3524 
3525         self.sections = []
3526         MAX_SIMULTANEOUS_ERRORS = 3
3527         for i in range(self.FILE_HEADER.NumberOfSections):
3528             if i >= MAX_SECTIONS:
3529                 self.__warnings.append(
3530                     "Too many sections {0} (>={1})".format(
3531                         self.FILE_HEADER.NumberOfSections, MAX_SECTIONS
3532                     )
3533                 )
3534                 break
3535             simultaneous_errors = 0
3536             section = SectionStructure(self.__IMAGE_SECTION_HEADER_format__, pe=self)
3537             if not section:
3538                 break
3539             section_offset = offset + section.sizeof() * i
3540             section.set_file_offset(section_offset)
3541             section_data = self.__data__[
3542                 section_offset : section_offset + section.sizeof()
3543             ]
3544             # Check if the section is all nulls and stop if so.
3545             if count_zeroes(section_data) == section.sizeof():
3546                 self.__warnings.append(f"Invalid section {i}. Contents are null-bytes.")
3547                 break
3548             if not section_data:
3549                 self.__warnings.append(
3550                     f"Invalid section {i}. No data in the file (is this corkami's "
3551                     "virtsectblXP?)."
3552                 )
3553                 break
3554             section.__unpack__(section_data)
3555             self.__structures__.append(section)
3556 
3557             if section.SizeOfRawData + section.PointerToRawData > len(self.__data__):
3558                 simultaneous_errors += 1
3559                 self.__warnings.append(
3560                     f"Error parsing section {i}. SizeOfRawData is larger than file."
3561                 )
3562 
3563             if self.adjust_FileAlignment(
3564                 section.PointerToRawData, self.OPTIONAL_HEADER.FileAlignment
3565             ) > len(self.__data__):
3566                 simultaneous_errors += 1
3567                 self.__warnings.append(
3568                     f"Error parsing section {i}. PointerToRawData points beyond "
3569                     "the end of the file."
3570                 )
3571 
3572             if section.Misc_VirtualSize > 0x10000000:
3573                 simultaneous_errors += 1
3574                 self.__warnings.append(
3575                     f"Suspicious value found parsing section {i}. VirtualSize is "
3576                     "extremely large > 256MiB."
3577                 )
3578 
3579             if (
3580                 self.adjust_SectionAlignment(
3581                     section.VirtualAddress,
3582                     self.OPTIONAL_HEADER.SectionAlignment,
3583                     self.OPTIONAL_HEADER.FileAlignment,
3584                 )
3585                 > 0x10000000
3586             ):
3587                 simultaneous_errors += 1
3588                 self.__warnings.append(
3589                     f"Suspicious value found parsing section {i}. VirtualAddress is "
3590                     "beyond 0x10000000."
3591                 )
3592 
3593             if (
3594                 self.OPTIONAL_HEADER.FileAlignment != 0
3595                 and (section.PointerToRawData % self.OPTIONAL_HEADER.FileAlignment) != 0
3596             ):
3597                 simultaneous_errors += 1
3598                 self.__warnings.append(
3599                     (
3600                         f"Error parsing section {i}. "
3601                         "PointerToRawData should normally be "
3602                         "a multiple of FileAlignment, this might imply the file "
3603                         "is trying to confuse tools which parse this incorrectly."
3604                     )
3605                 )
3606 
3607             if simultaneous_errors >= MAX_SIMULTANEOUS_ERRORS:
3608                 self.__warnings.append("Too many warnings parsing section. Aborting.")
3609                 break
3610 
3611             section_flags = retrieve_flags(SECTION_CHARACTERISTICS, "IMAGE_SCN_")
3612 
3613             # Set the section's flags according the the Characteristics member
3614             set_flags(section, section.Characteristics, section_flags)
3615 
3616             if section.__dict__.get(
3617                 "IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE", False
3618             ) and section.__dict__.get("IMAGE_SCN_MEM_EXECUTE", False):
3619 
3620                 if section.Name.rstrip(b"\x00") == b"PAGE" and self.is_driver():
3621                     # Drivers can have a PAGE section with those flags set without
3622                     # implying that it is malicious
3623                     pass
3624                 else:
3625                     self.__warnings.append(
3626                         f"Suspicious flags set for section {i}. "
3627                         "Both IMAGE_SCN_MEM_WRITE and IMAGE_SCN_MEM_EXECUTE are set. "
3628                         "This might indicate a packed executable."
3629                     )
3630 
3631             self.sections.append(section)
3632 
3633         # Sort the sections by their VirtualAddress and add a field to each of them
3634         # with the VirtualAddress of the next section. This will allow to check
3635         # for potentially overlapping sections in badly constructed PEs.
3636         self.sections.sort(key=lambda a: a.VirtualAddress)
3637         for idx, section in enumerate(self.sections):
3638             if idx == len(self.sections) - 1:
3639                 section.next_section_virtual_address = None
3640             else:
3641                 section.next_section_virtual_address = self.sections[
3642                     idx + 1
3643                 ].VirtualAddress
3644 
3645         if self.FILE_HEADER.NumberOfSections > 0 and self.sections:
3646             return (
3647                 offset + self.sections[0].sizeof() * self.FILE_HEADER.NumberOfSections
3648             )
3649         else:
3650             return offset

3652     def parse_data_directories(
3653         self, directories=None, forwarded_exports_only=False, import_dllnames_only=False
3654     ):
3655         """Parse and process the PE file's data directories. 
3656  
3657         If the optional argument 'directories' is given, only 
3658         the directories at the specified indexes will be parsed. 
3659         Such functionality allows parsing of areas of interest 
3660         without the burden of having to parse all others. 
3661         The directories can then be specified as: 
3662  
3663         For export / import only: 
3664  
3665           directories = [ 0, 1 ] 
3666  
3667         or (more verbosely): 
3668  
3669           directories = [ DIRECTORY_ENTRY['IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IMPORT'], 
3670             DIRECTORY_ENTRY['IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT'] ] 
3671  
3672         If 'directories' is a list, the ones that are processed will be removed, 
3673         leaving only the ones that are not present in the image. 
3674  
3675         If `forwarded_exports_only` is True, the IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT 
3676         attribute will only contain exports that are forwarded to another DLL. 
3677  
3678         If `import_dllnames_only` is True, symbols will not be parsed from 
3679         the import table and the entries in the IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IMPORT 
3680         attribute will not have a `symbols` attribute. 
3681         """
3682 
3683         directory_parsing = (
3684             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IMPORT", self.parse_import_directory),
3685             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT", self.parse_export_directory),
3686             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_RESOURCE", self.parse_resources_directory),
3687             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_DEBUG", self.parse_debug_directory),
3688             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_BASERELOC", self.parse_relocations_directory),
3689             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_TLS", self.parse_directory_tls),
3690             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_LOAD_CONFIG", self.parse_directory_load_config),
3691             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_DELAY_IMPORT", self.parse_delay_import_directory),
3692             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_BOUND_IMPORT", self.parse_directory_bound_imports),
3693             ("IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXCEPTION", self.parse_exceptions_directory),
3694         )
3695 
3696         if directories is not None:
3697             if not isinstance(directories, (tuple, list)):
3698                 directories = [directories]
3699 
3700         for entry in directory_parsing:
3701             # OC Patch:
3702             #
3703             try:
3704                 directory_index = DIRECTORY_ENTRY[entry[0]]
3705                 dir_entry = self.OPTIONAL_HEADER.DATA_DIRECTORY[directory_index]
3706             except IndexError:
3707                 break
3708 
3709             # Only process all the directories if no individual ones have
3710             # been chosen
3711             #
3712             if directories is None or directory_index in directories:
3713 
3714                 value = None
3715                 if dir_entry.VirtualAddress:
3716                     if (
3717                         forwarded_exports_only
3718                         and entry[0] == "IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_EXPORT"
3719                     ):
3720                         value = entry[1](
3721                             dir_entry.VirtualAddress,
3722                             dir_entry.Size,
3723                             forwarded_only=True,
3724                         )
3725                     elif (
3726                         import_dllnames_only
3727                         and entry[0] == "IMAGE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_IMPORT"
3728                     ):
3729                         value = entry[1](
3730                             dir_entry.VirtualAddress, dir_entry.Size, dllnames_only=True
3731                         )
3732 
3733                     else:
3734                         try:
3735                             value = entry[1](dir_entry.VirtualAddress, dir_entry.Size)
3736                         except PEFormatError as excp:
3737                             self.__warnings.append(
3738                                 f'Failed to process directoty "{entry[0]}": {excp}'
3739                             )
3740                     if value:
3741                         setattr(self, entry[0][6:], value)
3742 
3743             if (
3744                 (directories is not None)
3745                 and isinstance(directories, list)
3746                 and (entry[0] in directories)
3747             ):
3748                 directories.remove(directory_index)

3750     def parse_exceptions_directory(self, rva, size):
3751         """Parses exception directory 
3752  
3753         All the code related to handling exception directories is documented in 
3754         https://auscitte.github.io/systems%20blog/Exception-Directory-pefile#implementation-details 
3755         """
3756 
3757         # "For x64 and Itanium platforms; the format is different for other platforms"
3758         if (
3759             self.FILE_HEADER.Machine != MACHINE_TYPE["IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_AMD64"]
3760             and self.FILE_HEADER.Machine != MACHINE_TYPE["IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_IA64"]
3761         ):
3762             return None
3763 
3764         rf = Structure(self.__RUNTIME_FUNCTION_format__)
3765         rf_size = rf.sizeof()
3766         rva2rt = {}
3767         rt_funcs = []
3768         rva2infos = {}
3769         for _ in range(size // rf_size):
3770             rf = self.__unpack_data__(
3771                 self.__RUNTIME_FUNCTION_format__,
3772                 self.get_data(rva, rf_size),
3773                 file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva),
3774             )
3775 
3776             if rf is None:
3777                 break
3778 
3779             ui = None
3780 
3781             if (rf.UnwindData & 0x1) == 0:
3782                 # according to "Improving Automated Analysis of Windows x64 Binaries",
3783                 # if the lowest bit is set, (UnwindData & ~0x1) should point to the
3784                 # chained RUNTIME_FUNCTION instead of UNWIND_INFO
3785 
3786                 if (
3787                     rf.UnwindData in rva2infos
3788                 ):  # unwind info data structures can be shared among functions
3789                     ui = rva2infos[rf.UnwindData]
3790                 else:
3791                     ui = UnwindInfo(file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rf.UnwindData))
3792                     rva2infos[rf.UnwindData] = ui
3793 
3794                 ws = ui.unpack_in_stages(self.get_data(rf.UnwindData, ui.sizeof()))
3795                 if ws != None:
3796                     self.__warnings.append(ws)
3797                     break
3798                 ws = ui.unpack_in_stages(self.get_data(rf.UnwindData, ui.sizeof()))
3799                 if ws != None:
3800                     self.__warnings.append(ws)
3801                     break
3802 
3803                 self.__structures__.append(ui)
3804 
3805             entry = ExceptionsDirEntryData(struct=rf, unwindinfo=ui)
3806             rt_funcs.append(entry)
3807 
3808             rva2rt[rf.BeginAddress] = entry
3809             rva += rf_size
3810 
3811         # each chained function entry holds a reference to the function first in chain
3812         for rf in rt_funcs:
3813             if rf.unwindinfo is None:
3814                 # TODO: have not encountered such a binary yet;
3815                 # in theory, (UnwindData & ~0x1) should point to the chained
3816                 # RUNTIME_FUNCTION which could be used to locate the corresponding
3817                 # ExceptionsDirEntryData and set_chained_function_entry()
3818                 continue
3819             if not hasattr(rf.unwindinfo, "FunctionEntry"):
3820                 continue
3821             if not rf.unwindinfo.FunctionEntry in rva2rt:
3822                 self.__warnings.append(
3823                     f"FunctionEntry of UNWIND_INFO at {rf.struct.get_file_offset():x}"
3824                     " points to an entry that does not exist"
3825                 )
3826                 continue
3827             try:
3828                 rf.unwindinfo.set_chained_function_entry(
3829                     rva2rt[rf.unwindinfo.FunctionEntry]
3830                 )
3831             except PEFormatError as excp:
3832                 self.__warnings.append(
3833                     "Failed parsing FunctionEntry of UNWIND_INFO at "
3834                     f"{rf.struct.get_file_offset():x}: {excp}"
3835                 )
3836                 continue
3837 
3838         return rt_funcs

3840     def parse_directory_bound_imports(self, rva, size):
3841         """"""
3842 
3843         bnd_descr = Structure(self.__IMAGE_BOUND_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR_format__)
3844         bnd_descr_size = bnd_descr.sizeof()
3845         start = rva
3846 
3847         bound_imports = []
3848         while True:
3849             bnd_descr = self.__unpack_data__(
3850                 self.__IMAGE_BOUND_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR_format__,
3851                 self.__data__[rva : rva + bnd_descr_size],
3852                 file_offset=rva,
3853             )
3854             if bnd_descr is None:
3855                 # If can't parse directory then silently return.
3856                 # This directory does not necessarily have to be valid to
3857                 # still have a valid PE file
3858 
3859                 self.__warnings.append(
3860                     "The Bound Imports directory exists but can't be parsed."
3861                 )
3862 
3863                 return
3864 
3865             if bnd_descr.all_zeroes():
3866                 break
3867 
3868             rva += bnd_descr.sizeof()
3869 
3870             section = self.get_section_by_offset(rva)
3871             file_offset = self.get_offset_from_rva(rva)
3872             if section is None:
3873                 safety_boundary = len(self.__data__) - file_offset
3874                 sections_after_offset = [
3875                     s.PointerToRawData
3876                     for s in self.sections
3877                     if s.PointerToRawData > file_offset
3878                 ]
3879                 if sections_after_offset:
3880                     # Find the first section starting at a later offset than that
3881                     # specified by 'rva'
3882                     first_section_after_offset = min(sections_after_offset)
3883                     section = self.get_section_by_offset(first_section_after_offset)
3884                     if section is not None:
3885                         safety_boundary = section.PointerToRawData - file_offset
3886             else:
3887                 safety_boundary = (
3888                     section.PointerToRawData + len(section.get_data()) - file_offset
3889                 )
3890             if not section:
3891                 self.__warnings.append(
3892                     (
3893                         "RVA of IMAGE_BOUND_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR points "
3894                         "to an invalid address: {0:x}"
3895                     ).format(rva)
3896                 )
3897                 return
3898 
3899             forwarder_refs = []
3900             # 8 is the size of __IMAGE_BOUND_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR_format__
3901             for _ in range(
3902                 min(bnd_descr.NumberOfModuleForwarderRefs, int(safety_boundary / 8))
3903             ):
3904                 # Both structures IMAGE_BOUND_IMPORT_DESCRIPTOR and
3905                 # IMAGE_BOUND_FORWARDER_REF have the same size.
3906                 bnd_frwd_ref = self.__unpack_data__(
3907                     self.__IMAGE_BOUND_FORWARDER_REF_format__,
3908                     self.__data__[rva : rva + bnd_descr_size],
3909                     file_offset=rva,
3910                 )
3911                 # OC Patch:
3912                 if not bnd_frwd_ref:
3913                     raise PEFormatError("IMAGE_BOUND_FORWARDER_REF cannot be read")
3914                 rva += bnd_frwd_ref.sizeof()
3915 
3916                 offset = start + bnd_frwd_ref.OffsetModuleName
3917                 name_str = self.get_string_from_data(
3918                     0, self.__data__[offset : offset + MAX_STRING_LENGTH]
3919                 )
3920 
3921                 # OffsetModuleName points to a DLL name. These shouldn't be too long.
3922                 # Anything longer than a safety length of 128 will be taken to indicate
3923                 # a corrupt entry and abort the processing of these entries.
3924                 # Names shorter than 4 characters will be taken as invalid as well.
3925 
3926                 if name_str:
3927                     invalid_chars = [
3928                         c for c in bytearray(name_str) if chr(c) not in string.printable
3929                     ]
3930                     if len(name_str) > 256 or invalid_chars:
3931                         break
3932 
3933                 forwarder_refs.append(
3934                     BoundImportRefData(struct=bnd_frwd_ref, name=name_str)
3935                 )
3936 
3937             offset = start + bnd_descr.OffsetModuleName
3938             name_str = self.get_string_from_data(
3939                 0, self.__data__[offset : offset + MAX_STRING_LENGTH]
3940             )
3941 
3942             if name_str:
3943                 invalid_chars = [
3944                     c for c in bytearray(name_str) if chr(c) not in string.printable
3945                 ]
3946                 if len(name_str) > 256 or invalid_chars:
3947                     break
3948 
3949             if not name_str:
3950                 break
3951             bound_imports.append(
3952                 BoundImportDescData(
3953                     struct=bnd_descr, name=name_str, entries=forwarder_refs
3954                 )
3955             )
3956 
3957         return bound_imports

3987     def parse_directory_load_config(self, rva, size):
3988         """"""
3989 
3990         if self.PE_TYPE == OPTIONAL_HEADER_MAGIC_PE:
3991             load_config_dir_sz = self.get_dword_at_rva(rva)
3992             format = self.__IMAGE_LOAD_CONFIG_DIRECTORY_format__

3999                 "PE32+ file"

4017                 format,
4018                 self.get_data(rva, Structure(format).sizeof()),
4019                 file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva),
4020             )
4021         except PEFormatError:
4022             self.__warnings.append(
4023                 "Invalid LOAD_CONFIG information. Can't read " "data at RVA: 0x%x" % rva
4024             )
4025 
4026         if not load_config_struct:
4027             return None
4028 
4029         dynamic_relocations = None
4030         if fields_counter > 35:
4031             dynamic_relocations = self.parse_dynamic_relocations(
4032                 load_config_struct.DynamicValueRelocTableOffset,
4033                 load_config_struct.DynamicValueRelocTableSection,
4034             )

4037             struct=load_config_struct, dynamic_relocations=dynamic_relocations

4040     def parse_dynamic_relocations(
4041         self, dynamic_value_reloc_table_offset, dynamic_value_reloc_table_section
4042     ):
4043         if not dynamic_value_reloc_table_offset:
4044             return None
4045         if not dynamic_value_reloc_table_section:
4046             return None
4047 
4048         if dynamic_value_reloc_table_section > len(self.sections):
4049             return None
4050 
4051         section = self.sections[dynamic_value_reloc_table_section - 1]
4052         rva = section.VirtualAddress + dynamic_value_reloc_table_offset
4053         image_dynamic_reloc_table_struct = None
4054         reloc_table_size = Structure(
4055             self.__IMAGE_DYNAMIC_RELOCATION_TABLE_format__
4056         ).sizeof()
4057         try:
4058             image_dynamic_reloc_table_struct = self.__unpack_data__(
4059                 self.__IMAGE_DYNAMIC_RELOCATION_TABLE_format__,
4060                 self.get_data(rva, reloc_table_size),
4061                 file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva),
4062             )
4063         except PEFormatError:
4064             self.__warnings.append(
4065                 "Invalid IMAGE_DYNAMIC_RELOCATION_TABLE information. Can't read "
4066                 "data at RVA: 0x%x" % rva
4067             )
4068 
4069         if image_dynamic_reloc_table_struct.Version != 1:
4070             self.__warnings.append(
4071                 "No pasring available for IMAGE_DYNAMIC_RELOCATION_TABLE.Version = %d",
4072                 image_dynamic_reloc_table_struct.Version,
4073             )
4074             return None
4075 
4076         rva += reloc_table_size
4077         end = rva + image_dynamic_reloc_table_struct.Size
4078         dynamic_relocations = []
4079 
4080         while rva < end:
4081             format = self.__IMAGE_DYNAMIC_RELOCATION_format__
4082 
4083             if self.PE_TYPE == OPTIONAL_HEADER_MAGIC_PE_PLUS:
4084                 format = self.__IMAGE_DYNAMIC_RELOCATION64_format__
4085 
4086             rlc_size = Structure(format).sizeof()
4087 
4088             try:
4089                 dynamic_rlc = self.__unpack_data__(
4090                     format,
4091                     self.get_data(rva, rlc_size),
4092                     file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva),
4093                 )
4094             except PEFormatError:
4095                 self.__warnings.append(
4096                     "Invalid relocation information. Can't read "
4097                     "data at RVA: 0x%x" % rva
4098                 )
4099                 dynamic_rlc = None
4100 
4101             if not dynamic_rlc:
4102                 break
4103 
4104             rva += rlc_size
4105             symbol = dynamic_rlc.Symbol
4106             size = dynamic_rlc.BaseRelocSize
4107 
4108             if 3 <= symbol <= 5:
4109                 relocations = self.parse_image_base_relocation_list(
4110                     rva, size, self.dynamic_relocation_format_by_symbol[symbol]
4111                 )
4112                 dynamic_relocations.append(
4113                     DynamicRelocationData(
4114                         struct=dynamic_rlc, symbol=symbol, relocations=relocations
4115                     )
4116                 )
4117 
4118             if symbol > 5:
4119                 relocations = self.parse_image_base_relocation_list(rva, size)
4120                 dynamic_relocations.append(
4121                     DynamicRelocationData(
4122                         struct=dynamic_rlc, symbol=symbol, relocations=relocations
4123                     )
4124                 )
4125 
4126             rva += size
4127 
4128         return dynamic_relocations

4135     def parse_image_base_relocation_list(self, rva, size, fmt=None):
4136         rlc_size = Structure(self.__IMAGE_BASE_RELOCATION_format__).sizeof()
4137         end = rva + size
4138 
4139         relocations = []
4140         while rva < end:
4141 
4142             # OC Patch:
4143             # Malware that has bad RVA entries will cause an error.
4144             # Just continue on after an exception
4145             #
4146             try:
4147                 rlc = self.__unpack_data__(
4148                     self.__IMAGE_BASE_RELOCATION_format__,
4149                     self.get_data(rva, rlc_size),
4150                     file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva),
4151                 )
4152             except PEFormatError:
4153                 self.__warnings.append(
4154                     "Invalid relocation information. Can't read "
4155                     "data at RVA: 0x%x" % rva
4156                 )
4157                 rlc = None
4158 
4159             if not rlc:
4160                 break
4161 
4162             # rlc.VirtualAddress must lie within the Image
4163             if rlc.VirtualAddress > self.OPTIONAL_HEADER.SizeOfImage:
4164                 self.__warnings.append(
4165                     "Invalid relocation information. VirtualAddress outside"
4166                     " of Image: 0x%x" % rlc.VirtualAddress
4167                 )
4168                 break
4169 
4170             # rlc.SizeOfBlock must be less or equal than the size of the image
4171             # (It's a rather loose sanity test)
4172             if rlc.SizeOfBlock > self.OPTIONAL_HEADER.SizeOfImage:
4173                 self.__warnings.append(
4174                     "Invalid relocation information. SizeOfBlock too large"
4175                     ": %d" % rlc.SizeOfBlock
4176                 )
4177                 break
4178 
4179             if fmt is None:
4180                 reloc_entries = self.parse_relocations(
4181                     rva + rlc_size, rlc.VirtualAddress, rlc.SizeOfBlock - rlc_size
4182                 )
4183             else:
4184                 reloc_entries = self.parse_relocations_with_format(
4185                     rva + rlc_size, rlc.VirtualAddress, rlc.SizeOfBlock - rlc_size, fmt
4186                 )
4187 
4188             relocations.append(BaseRelocationData(struct=rlc, entries=reloc_entries))
4189 
4190             if not rlc.SizeOfBlock:
4191                 break
4192             rva += rlc.SizeOfBlock
4193 
4194         return relocations

4196     def parse_relocations(self, data_rva, rva, size):
4197         """"""
4198 
4199         try:
4200             data = self.get_data(data_rva, size)
4201             file_offset = self.get_offset_from_rva(data_rva)
4202         except PEFormatError:
4203             self.__warnings.append(f"Bad RVA in relocation data: 0x{data_rva:x}")
4204             return []
4205 
4206         entries = []
4207         offsets_and_type = set()
4208         for idx in range(int(len(data) / 2)):
4209 
4210             entry = self.__unpack_data__(
4211                 self.__IMAGE_BASE_RELOCATION_ENTRY_format__,
4212                 data[idx * 2 : (idx + 1) * 2],
4213                 file_offset=file_offset,
4214             )
4215 
4216             if not entry:
4217                 break
4218             word = entry.Data
4219 
4220             reloc_type = word >> 12
4221             reloc_offset = word & 0x0FFF
4222             if (reloc_offset, reloc_type) in offsets_and_type:
4223                 self.__warnings.append(
4224                     "Overlapping offsets in relocation data "
4225                     "at RVA: 0x%x" % (reloc_offset + rva)
4226                 )
4227                 break
4228 
4229             offsets_and_type.add((reloc_offset, reloc_type))
4230 
4231             entries.append(
4232                 RelocationData(
4233                     struct=entry, type=reloc_type, base_rva=rva, rva=reloc_offset + rva
4234                 )
4235             )
4236             file_offset += entry.sizeof()
4237 
4238         return entries
4239 
4240     def parse_relocations_with_format(self, data_rva, rva, size, format):
4241         """"""
4242 
4243         try:
4244             data = self.get_data(data_rva, size)
4245             file_offset = self.get_offset_from_rva(data_rva)
4246         except PEFormatError:
4247             self.__warnings.append(f"Bad RVA in relocation data: 0x{data_rva:x}")
4248             return []
4249 
4250         entry_size = StructureWithBitfields(format).sizeof()
4251         entries = []
4252         offsets = set()
4253         for idx in range(int(len(data) / entry_size)):
4254 
4255             entry = self.__unpack_data_with_bitfields__(
4256                 format,
4257                 data[idx * entry_size : (idx + 1) * entry_size],
4258                 file_offset=file_offset,
4259             )
4260 
4261             if not entry:
4262                 break
4263 
4264             reloc_offset = entry.PageRelativeOffset
4265             if reloc_offset in offsets:
4266                 self.__warnings.append(
4267                     "Overlapping offsets in relocation data "
4268                     "at RVA: 0x%x" % (reloc_offset + rva)
4269                 )
4270                 break
4271             offsets.add(reloc_offset)
4272 
4273             entries.append(
4274                 RelocationData(struct=entry, base_rva=rva, rva=reloc_offset + rva)
4275             )
4276             file_offset += entry_size
4277 
4278         return entries

4280     def parse_debug_directory(self, rva, size):
4281         """"""
4282 
4283         dbg_size = Structure(self.__IMAGE_DEBUG_DIRECTORY_format__).sizeof()
4284 
4285         debug = []
4286         for idx in range(int(size / dbg_size)):
4287             try:
4288                 data = self.get_data(rva + dbg_size * idx, dbg_size)
4289             except PEFormatError:
4290                 self.__warnings.append(
4291                     "Invalid debug information. Can't read " "data at RVA: 0x%x" % rva
4292                 )
4293                 return None
4294 
4295             dbg = self.__unpack_data__(
4296                 self.__IMAGE_DEBUG_DIRECTORY_format__,
4297                 data,
4298                 file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva + dbg_size * idx),
4299             )
4300 
4301             if not dbg:
4302                 return None
4303 
4304             # apply structure according to DEBUG_TYPE
4305             # http://www.debuginfo.com/articles/debuginfomatch.html
4306             #
4307             dbg_type = None
4308 
4309             if dbg.Type == 1:
4310                 # IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_COFF
4311                 pass
4312 
4313             elif dbg.Type == 2:
4314                 # if IMAGE_DEBUG_TYPE_CODEVIEW
4315                 dbg_type_offset = dbg.PointerToRawData
4316                 dbg_type_size = dbg.SizeOfData
4317                 dbg_type_data = self.__data__[
4318                     dbg_type_offset : dbg_type_offset + dbg_type_size
4319                 ]
4320 
4321                 if dbg_type_data[:4] == b"RSDS":
4322                     # pdb7.0
4323                     __CV_INFO_PDB70_format__ = [
4324                         "CV_INFO_PDB70",
4325                         [
4326                             "4s,CvSignature",
4327                             "I,Signature_Data1",  # Signature is of GUID type
4328                             "H,Signature_Data2",
4329                             "H,Signature_Data3",
4330                             "B,Signature_Data4",
4331                             "B,Signature_Data5",
4332                             "6s,Signature_Data6",
4333                             "I,Age",
4334                         ],
4335                     ]
4336                     pdbFileName_size = (
4337                         dbg_type_size - Structure(__CV_INFO_PDB70_format__).sizeof()
4338                     )
4339 
4340                     # pdbFileName_size can be negative here, as seen in the malware
4341                     # sample with hash
4342                     # MD5: 7c297600870d026c014d42596bb9b5fd
4343                     # SHA256:
4344                     #   83f4e63681fcba8a9d7bbb1688c71981b1837446514a1773597e0192bba9fac3
4345                     # Checking for positive size here to ensure proper parsing.
4346                     if pdbFileName_size > 0:
4347                         __CV_INFO_PDB70_format__[1].append(
4348                             "{0}s,PdbFileName".format(pdbFileName_size)
4349                         )
4350                     dbg_type = self.__unpack_data__(
4351                         __CV_INFO_PDB70_format__, dbg_type_data, dbg_type_offset
4352                     )
4353                     if dbg_type is not None:
4354                         dbg_type.Signature_Data6_value = struct.unpack(
4355                             ">Q", b"\0\0" + dbg_type.Signature_Data6
4356                         )[0]
4357                         dbg_type.Signature_String = (
4358                             str(
4359                                 uuid.UUID(
4360                                     fields=(
4361                                         dbg_type.Signature_Data1,
4362                                         dbg_type.Signature_Data2,

4398                         __CV_INFO_PDB20_format__, dbg_type_data, dbg_type_offset

4406                     dbg_type_offset : dbg_type_offset + dbg_type_size

4451     def parse_resources_directory(self, rva, size=0, base_rva=None, level=0, dirs=None):
4452         """Parse the resources directory. 
4453  
4454         Given the RVA of the resources directory, it will process all 
4455         its entries. 
4456  
4457         The root will have the corresponding member of its structure, 
4458         IMAGE_RESOURCE_DIRECTORY plus 'entries', a list of all the 
4459         entries in the directory. 
4460  
4461         Those entries will have, correspondingly, all the structure's 
4462         members (IMAGE_RESOURCE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY) and an additional one, 
4463         "directory", pointing to the IMAGE_RESOURCE_DIRECTORY structure 
4464         representing upper layers of the tree. This one will also have 
4465         an 'entries' attribute, pointing to the 3rd, and last, level. 
4466         Another directory with more entries. Those last entries will 
4467         have a new attribute (both 'leaf' or 'data_entry' can be used to 
4468         access it). This structure finally points to the resource data. 
4469         All the members of this structure, IMAGE_RESOURCE_DATA_ENTRY, 
4470         are available as its attributes. 
4471         """
4472 
4473         # OC Patch:
4474         if dirs is None:
4475             dirs = [rva]
4476 
4477         if base_rva is None:
4478             base_rva = rva
4479 
4480         if level > MAX_RESOURCE_DEPTH:
4481             self.__warnings.append(
4482                 "Error parsing the resources directory. "
4483                 "Excessively nested table depth %d (>%s)" % (level, MAX_RESOURCE_DEPTH)
4484             )
4485             return None
4486 
4487         try:
4488             # If the RVA is invalid all would blow up. Some EXEs seem to be
4489             # specially nasty and have an invalid RVA.
4490             data = self.get_data(
4491                 rva, Structure(self.__IMAGE_RESOURCE_DIRECTORY_format__).sizeof()
4492             )
4493         except PEFormatError:
4494             self.__warnings.append(
4495                 "Invalid resources directory. Can't read "
4496                 "directory data at RVA: 0x%x" % rva
4497             )
4498             return None
4499 
4500         # Get the resource directory structure, that is, the header
4501         # of the table preceding the actual entries
4502         #
4503         resource_dir = self.__unpack_data__(
4504             self.__IMAGE_RESOURCE_DIRECTORY_format__,
4505             data,
4506             file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva),
4507         )
4508         if resource_dir is None:
4509             # If we can't parse resources directory then silently return.
4510             # This directory does not necessarily have to be valid to
4511             # still have a valid PE file
4512             self.__warnings.append(
4513                 "Invalid resources directory. Can't parse "
4514                 "directory data at RVA: 0x%x" % rva
4515             )
4516             return None
4517 
4518         dir_entries = []
4519 
4520         # Advance the RVA to the position immediately following the directory
4521         # table header and pointing to the first entry in the table
4522         #
4523         rva += resource_dir.sizeof()
4524 
4525         number_of_entries = (
4526             resource_dir.NumberOfNamedEntries + resource_dir.NumberOfIdEntries
4527         )
4528 
4529         # Set a hard limit on the maximum reasonable number of entries
4530         MAX_ALLOWED_ENTRIES = 4096
4531         if number_of_entries > MAX_ALLOWED_ENTRIES:
4532             self.__warnings.append(
4533                 "Error parsing the resources directory. "
4534                 "The directory contains %d entries (>%s)"
4535                 % (number_of_entries, MAX_ALLOWED_ENTRIES)
4536             )
4537             return None
4538 
4539         self.__total_resource_entries_count += number_of_entries
4540         if self.__total_resource_entries_count > MAX_RESOURCE_ENTRIES:
4541             self.__warnings.append(
4542                 "Error parsing the resources directory. "
4543                 "The file contains at least %d entries (>%d)"
4544                 % (self.__total_resource_entries_count, MAX_RESOURCE_ENTRIES)
4545             )
4546             return None
4547 
4548         strings_to_postprocess = []
4549 
4550         # Keep track of the last name's start and end offsets in order
4551         # to be able to detect overlapping entries that might suggest
4552         # and invalid or corrupt directory.
4553         last_name_begin_end = None
4554         for idx in range(number_of_entries):
4555             if (
4556                 not self.__resource_size_limit_reached
4557                 and self.__total_resource_bytes > self.__resource_size_limit_upperbounds
4558             ):
4559 
4560                 self.__resource_size_limit_reached = True
4561                 self.__warnings.append(
4562                     "Resource size 0x%x exceeds file size 0x%x, overlapping "
4563                     "resources found."
4564                     % (
4565                         self.__total_resource_bytes,
4566                         self.__resource_size_limit_upperbounds,
4567                     )
4568                 )
4569 
4570             res = self.parse_resource_entry(rva)
4571             if res is None:
4572                 self.__warnings.append(
4573                     "Error parsing the resources directory, "
4574                     "Entry %d is invalid, RVA = 0x%x. " % (idx, rva)
4575                 )
4576                 break
4577 
4578             entry_name = None
4579             entry_id = None
4580 
4581             name_is_string = (res.Name & 0x80000000) >> 31
4582             if not name_is_string:
4583                 entry_id = res.Name
4584             else:
4585                 ustr_offset = base_rva + res.NameOffset
4586                 try:
4587                     entry_name = UnicodeStringWrapperPostProcessor(self, ustr_offset)
4588                     self.__total_resource_bytes += entry_name.get_pascal_16_length()
4589                     # If the last entry's offset points before the current's but its end
4590                     # is past the current's beginning, assume the overlap indicates a
4591                     # corrupt name.
4592                     if last_name_begin_end and (
4593                         last_name_begin_end[0] < ustr_offset
4594                         and last_name_begin_end[1] >= ustr_offset
4595                     ):
4596                         # Remove the previous overlapping entry as it's likely to be
4597                         # already corrupt data.
4598                         strings_to_postprocess.pop()
4599                         self.__warnings.append(
4600                             "Error parsing the resources directory, "
4601                             "attempting to read entry name. "
4602                             "Entry names overlap 0x%x" % (ustr_offset)
4603                         )
4604                         break
4605 
4606                     last_name_begin_end = (
4607                         ustr_offset,
4608                         ustr_offset + entry_name.get_pascal_16_length(),
4609                     )
4610 
4611                     strings_to_postprocess.append(entry_name)
4612 
4613                 except PEFormatError:
4614                     self.__warnings.append(
4615                         "Error parsing the resources directory, "
4616                         "attempting to read entry name. "
4617                         "Can't read unicode string at offset 0x%x" % (ustr_offset)
4618                     )
4619 
4620             if res.DataIsDirectory:
4621                 # OC Patch:
4622                 #
4623                 # One trick malware can do is to recursively reference
4624                 # the next directory. This causes hilarity to ensue when
4625                 # trying to parse everything correctly.
4626                 # If the original RVA given to this function is equal to
4627                 # the next one to parse, we assume that it's a trick.
4628                 # Instead of raising a PEFormatError this would skip some
4629                 # reasonable data so we just break.
4630                 #
4631                 # 9ee4d0a0caf095314fd7041a3e4404dc is the offending sample
4632                 if base_rva + res.OffsetToDirectory in dirs:
4633                     break
4634 
4635                 entry_directory = self.parse_resources_directory(
4636                     base_rva + res.OffsetToDirectory,
4637                     size - (rva - base_rva),  # size
4638                     base_rva=base_rva,
4639                     level=level + 1,
4640                     dirs=dirs + [base_rva + res.OffsetToDirectory],
4641                 )
4642 
4643                 if not entry_directory:
4644                     break
4645 
4646                 # Ange Albertini's code to process resources' strings
4647                 #
4648                 strings = None
4649                 if entry_id == RESOURCE_TYPE["RT_STRING"]:
4650                     strings = {}
4651                     for resource_id in entry_directory.entries:
4652                         if hasattr(resource_id, "directory"):
4653 
4654                             resource_strings = {}
4655 
4656                             for resource_lang in resource_id.directory.entries:
4657 
4658                                 if (
4659                                     resource_lang is None
4660                                     or not hasattr(resource_lang, "data")
4661                                     or resource_lang.data.struct.Size is None
4662                                     or resource_id.id is None
4663                                 ):
4664                                     continue
4665 
4666                                 string_entry_rva = (
4667                                     resource_lang.data.struct.OffsetToData
4668                                 )
4669                                 string_entry_size = resource_lang.data.struct.Size
4670                                 string_entry_id = resource_id.id
4671 
4672                                 # XXX: has been raising exceptions preventing parsing
4673                                 try:
4674                                     string_entry_data = self.get_data(
4675                                         string_entry_rva, string_entry_size
4676                                     )
4677                                 except PEFormatError:
4678                                     self.__warnings.append(
4679                                         f"Error parsing resource of type RT_STRING at "
4680                                         f"RVA 0x{string_entry_rva:x} with "
4681                                         f"size {string_entry_size}"
4682                                     )
4683                                     continue
4684 
4685                                 parse_strings(
4686                                     string_entry_data,
4687                                     (int(string_entry_id) - 1) * 16,
4688                                     resource_strings,
4689                                 )
4690                                 strings.update(resource_strings)
4691 
4692                             resource_id.directory.strings = resource_strings
4693 
4694                 dir_entries.append(
4695                     ResourceDirEntryData(
4696                         struct=res,
4697                         name=entry_name,
4698                         id=entry_id,
4699                         directory=entry_directory,
4700                     )
4701                 )
4702 
4703             else:
4704                 struct = self.parse_resource_data_entry(
4705                     base_rva + res.OffsetToDirectory
4706                 )
4707 
4708                 if struct:
4709                     self.__total_resource_bytes += struct.Size
4710                     entry_data = ResourceDataEntryData(
4711                         struct=struct, lang=res.Name & 0x3FF, sublang=res.Name >> 10
4712                     )
4713 
4714                     dir_entries.append(
4715                         ResourceDirEntryData(
4716                             struct=res, name=entry_name, id=entry_id, data=entry_data
4717                         )
4718                     )
4719 
4720                 else:
4721                     break
4722 
4723             # Check if this entry contains version information
4724             #
4725             if level == 0 and res.Id == RESOURCE_TYPE["RT_VERSION"]:
4726                 if dir_entries:
4727                     last_entry = dir_entries[-1]
4728 
4729                 try:
4730                     version_entries = last_entry.directory.entries[0].directory.entries
4731                 except:
4732                     # Maybe a malformed directory structure...?
4733                     # Let's ignore it
4734                     pass
4735                 else:
4736                     for version_entry in version_entries:
4737                         rt_version_struct = None
4738                         try:
4739                             rt_version_struct = version_entry.data.struct
4740                         except:
4741                             # Maybe a malformed directory structure...?
4742                             # Let's ignore it
4743                             pass
4744 
4745                         if rt_version_struct is not None:
4746                             self.parse_version_information(rt_version_struct)
4747 
4748             rva += res.sizeof()
4749 
4750         string_rvas = [s.get_rva() for s in strings_to_postprocess]
4751         string_rvas.sort()
4752 
4753         for idx, s in enumerate(strings_to_postprocess):
4754             s.render_pascal_16()
4755 
4756         resource_directory_data = ResourceDirData(
4757             struct=resource_dir, entries=dir_entries
4758         )
4759 
4760         return resource_directory_data

4762     def parse_resource_data_entry(self, rva):
4763         """Parse a data entry from the resources directory."""
4764 
4765         try:
4766             # If the RVA is invalid all would blow up. Some EXEs seem to be
4767             # specially nasty and have an invalid RVA.
4768             data = self.get_data(
4769                 rva, Structure(self.__IMAGE_RESOURCE_DATA_ENTRY_format__).sizeof()
4770             )
4771         except PEFormatError:
4772             self.__warnings.append(
4773                 "Error parsing a resource directory data entry, "
4774                 "the RVA is invalid: 0x%x" % (rva)
4775             )
4776             return None
4777 
4778         data_entry = self.__unpack_data__(
4779             self.__IMAGE_RESOURCE_DATA_ENTRY_format__,
4780             data,
4781             file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva),
4782         )
4783 
4784         return data_entry

4786     def parse_resource_entry(self, rva):
4787         """Parse a directory entry from the resources directory."""
4788 
4789         try:
4790             data = self.get_data(
4791                 rva, Structure(self.__IMAGE_RESOURCE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_format__).sizeof()
4792             )
4793         except PEFormatError:
4794             # A warning will be added by the caller if this method returns None
4795             return None
4796 
4797         resource = self.__unpack_data__(
4798             self.__IMAGE_RESOURCE_DIRECTORY_ENTRY_format__,
4799             data,
4800             file_offset=self.get_offset_from_rva(rva),
4801         )
4802 
4803         if resource is None:
4804             return None
4805 
4806         # resource.NameIsString = (resource.Name & 0x80000000L) >> 31
4807         resource.NameOffset = resource.Name & 0x7FFFFFFF
4808 
4809         resource.__pad = resource.Name & 0xFFFF0000
4810         resource.Id = resource.Name & 0x0000FFFF
4811 
4812         resource.DataIsDirectory = (resource.OffsetToData & 0x80000000) >> 31
4813         resource.OffsetToDirectory = resource.OffsetToData & 0x7FFFFFFF
4814 
4815         return resource

4817     def parse_version_information(self, version_struct):
4818         """Parse version information structure. 
4819  
4820         The date will be made available in three attributes of the PE object. 
4821  
4822         VS_VERSIONINFO   will contain the first three fields of the main structure: 
4823             'Length', 'ValueLength', and 'Type' 
4824  
4825         VS_FIXEDFILEINFO will hold the rest of the fields, accessible as sub-attributes: 
4826             'Signature', 'StrucVersion', 'FileVersionMS', 'FileVersionLS', 
4827             'ProductVersionMS', 'ProductVersionLS', 'FileFlagsMask', 'FileFlags', 
4828             'FileOS', 'FileType', 'FileSubtype', 'FileDateMS', 'FileDateLS' 
4829  
4830         FileInfo    is a list of all StringFileInfo and VarFileInfo structures. 
4831  
4832         StringFileInfo structures will have a list as an attribute named 'StringTable' 
4833         containing all the StringTable structures. Each of those structures contains a 
4834         dictionary 'entries' with all the key / value version information string pairs. 
4835  
4836         VarFileInfo structures will have a list as an attribute named 'Var' containing 
4837         all Var structures. Each Var structure will have a dictionary as an attribute 
4838         named 'entry' which will contain the name and value of the Var. 
4839         """
4840 
4841         # Retrieve the data for the version info resource
4842         #
4843         try:
4844             start_offset = self.get_offset_from_rva(version_struct.OffsetToData)
4845         except PEFormatError:
4846             self.__warnings.append(
4847                 "Error parsing the version information, "
4848                 "attempting to read OffsetToData with RVA: 0x{:x}".format(
4849                     version_struct.OffsetToData
4850                 )
4851             )
4852             return
4853         raw_data = self.__data__[start_offset : start_offset + version_struct.Size]
4854 
4855         # Map the main structure and the subsequent string
4856         #
4857         versioninfo_struct = self.__unpack_data__(
4858             self.__VS_VERSIONINFO_format__, raw_data, file_offset=start_offset
4859         )
4860 
4861         if versioninfo_struct is None:
4862             return
4863 
4864         ustr_offset = version_struct.OffsetToData + versioninfo_struct.sizeof()
4865         section = self.get_section_by_rva(ustr_offset)
4866         section_end = None
4867         if section:
4868             section_end = section.VirtualAddress + max(
4869                 section.SizeOfRawData, section.Misc_VirtualSize
4870             )
4871 
4872         versioninfo_string = None
4873         # These should return 'ascii' decoded data. For the case when it's
4874         # garbled data the ascii string will retain the byte values while
4875         # encoding it to something else may yield values that don't match the
4876         # file's contents.
4877         try:
4878             if section_end is None:
4879                 versioninfo_string = self.get_string_u_at_rva(
4880                     ustr_offset, encoding="ascii"
4881                 )
4882             else:
4883                 versioninfo_string = self.get_string_u_at_rva(
4884                     ustr_offset, (section_end - ustr_offset) >> 1, encoding="ascii"
4885                 )
4886         except PEFormatError:
4887             self.__warnings.append(
4888                 "Error parsing the version information, "
4889                 "attempting to read VS_VERSION_INFO string. Can't "
4890                 "read unicode string at offset 0x%x" % (ustr_offset)
4891             )
4892 
4893         if versioninfo_string is None:
4894             self.__warnings.append(
4895                 "Invalid VS_VERSION_INFO block: {0}".format(versioninfo_string)
4896             )
4897             return
4898 
4899         # If the structure does not contain the expected name, it's assumed to
4900         # be invalid
4901         if versioninfo_string is not None and versioninfo_string != b"VS_VERSION_INFO":
4902             if len(versioninfo_string) > 128:
4903                 excerpt = versioninfo_string[:128].decode("ascii")
4904                 # Don't leave any half-escaped characters
4905                 excerpt = excerpt[: excerpt.rfind("\\u")]
4906                 versioninfo_string = b(
4907                     "{0} ... ({1} bytes, too long to display)".format(
4908                         excerpt, len(versioninfo_string)
4909                     )
4910                 )
4911             self.__warnings.append(
4912                 "Invalid VS_VERSION_INFO block: {0}".format(
4913                     versioninfo_string.decode("ascii").replace("\00", "\\00")
4914                 )
4915             )
4916             return
4917 
4918         if not hasattr(self, "VS_VERSIONINFO"):
4919             self.VS_VERSIONINFO = []
4920 
4921         # Set the PE object's VS_VERSIONINFO to this one
4922         vinfo = versioninfo_struct
4923 
4924         # Set the Key attribute to point to the unicode string identifying the structure
4925         vinfo.Key = versioninfo_string
4926 
4927         self.VS_VERSIONINFO.append(vinfo)
4928 
4929         if versioninfo_string is None:
4930             versioninfo_string = ""
4931         # Process the fixed version information, get the offset and structure
4932         fixedfileinfo_offset = self.dword_align(
4933             versioninfo_struct.sizeof() + 2 * (len(versioninfo_string) + 1),
4934             version_struct.OffsetToData,
4935         )
4936         fixedfileinfo_struct = self.__unpack_data__(
4937             self.__VS_FIXEDFILEINFO_format__,
4938             raw_data[fixedfileinfo_offset:],
4939             file_offset=start_offset + fixedfileinfo_offset,
4940         )
4941 
4942         if not fixedfileinfo_struct:
4943             return
4944 
4945         if not hasattr(self, "VS_FIXEDFILEINFO"):
4946             self.VS_FIXEDFILEINFO = []
4947 
4948         # Set the PE object's VS_FIXEDFILEINFO to this one
4949         self.VS_FIXEDFILEINFO.append(fixedfileinfo_struct)
4950 
4951         # Start parsing all the StringFileInfo and VarFileInfo structures
4952 
4953         # Get the first one
4954         stringfileinfo_offset = self.dword_align(
4955             fixedfileinfo_offset + fixedfileinfo_struct.sizeof(),
4956             version_struct.OffsetToData,
4957         )
4958 
4959         # Set the PE object's attribute that will contain them all.
4960         if not hasattr(self, "FileInfo"):
4961             self.FileInfo = []
4962 
4963         finfo = []
4964         while True:
4965 
4966             # Process the StringFileInfo/VarFileInfo structure
4967             stringfileinfo_struct = self.__unpack_data__(
4968                 self.__StringFileInfo_format__,
4969                 raw_data[stringfileinfo_offset:],
4970                 file_offset=start_offset + stringfileinfo_offset,
4971             )
4972 
4973             if stringfileinfo_struct is None:
4974                 self.__warnings.append(
4975                     "Error parsing StringFileInfo/VarFileInfo struct"
4976                 )
4977                 return None
4978 
4979             # Get the subsequent string defining the structure.
4980             ustr_offset = (
4981                 version_struct.OffsetToData
4982                 + stringfileinfo_offset
4983                 + versioninfo_struct.sizeof()
4984             )
4985             try:
4986                 stringfileinfo_string = self.get_string_u_at_rva(ustr_offset)
4987             except PEFormatError:
4988                 self.__warnings.append(
4989                     "Error parsing the version information, "
4990                     "attempting to read StringFileInfo string. Can't "
4991                     "read unicode string at offset 0x{0:x}".format(ustr_offset)
4992                 )
4993                 break
4994 
4995             # Set such string as the Key attribute
4996             stringfileinfo_struct.Key = stringfileinfo_string
4997 
4998             # Append the structure to the PE object's list
4999             finfo.append(stringfileinfo_struct)
5000 
5001             # Parse a StringFileInfo entry
5002             if stringfileinfo_string and stringfileinfo_string.startswith(
5003                 b"StringFileInfo"
5004             ):
5005 
5006                 if (
5007                     stringfileinfo_struct.Type in (0, 1)
5008                     and stringfileinfo_struct.ValueLength == 0
5009                 ):
5010 
5011                     stringtable_offset = self.dword_align(
5012                         stringfileinfo_offset
5013                         + stringfileinfo_struct.sizeof()
5014                         + 2 * (len(stringfileinfo_string) + 1),
5015                         version_struct.OffsetToData,
5016                     )
5017 
5018                     stringfileinfo_struct.StringTable = []
5019 
5020                     # Process the String Table entries
5021                     while True:
5022 
5023                         stringtable_struct = self.__unpack_data__(
5024                             self.__StringTable_format__,
5025                             raw_data[stringtable_offset:],
5026                             file_offset=start_offset + stringtable_offset,
5027                         )
5028 
5029                         if not stringtable_struct:
5030                             break
5031 
5032                         ustr_offset = (
5033                             version_struct.OffsetToData
5034                             + stringtable_offset
5035                             + stringtable_struct.sizeof()
5036                         )
5037                         try:
5038                             stringtable_string = self.get_string_u_at_rva(ustr_offset)
5039                         except PEFormatError:
5040                             self.__warnings.append(
5041                                 "Error parsing the version information, "
5042                                 "attempting to read StringTable string. Can't "
5043                                 "read unicode string at offset 0x{0:x}".format(
5044                                     ustr_offset
5045                                 )
5046                             )
5047                             break
5048 
5049                         stringtable_struct.LangID = stringtable_string
5050                         stringtable_struct.entries = {}
5051                         stringtable_struct.entries_offsets = {}
5052                         stringtable_struct.entries_lengths = {}
5053                         stringfileinfo_struct.StringTable.append(stringtable_struct)
5054 
5055                         entry_offset = self.dword_align(
5056                             stringtable_offset
5057                             + stringtable_struct.sizeof()
5058                             + 2 * (len(stringtable_string) + 1),
5059                             version_struct.OffsetToData,
5060                         )
5061 
5062                         # Process all entries in the string table
5063 
5064                         while (
5065                             entry_offset
5066                             < stringtable_offset + stringtable_struct.Length
5067                         ):
5068 
5069                             string_struct = self.__unpack_data__(
5070                                 self.__String_format__,
5071                                 raw_data[entry_offset:],
5072                                 file_offset=start_offset + entry_offset,
5073                             )
5074 
5075                             if not string_struct:
5076                                 break
5077 
5078                             ustr_offset = (
5079                                 version_struct.OffsetToData
5080                                 + entry_offset
5081                                 + string_struct.sizeof()
5082                             )
5083                             try:
5084                                 key = self.get_string_u_at_rva(ustr_offset)
5085                                 key_offset = self.get_offset_from_rva(ustr_offset)
5086                             except PEFormatError:
5087                                 self.__warnings.append(
5088                                     "Error parsing the version information, "
5089                                     "attempting to read StringTable Key string. Can't "
5090                                     "read unicode string at offset 0x{0:x}".format(
5091                                         ustr_offset
5092                                     )
5093                                 )
5094                                 break
5095 
5096                             value_offset = self.dword_align(
5097                                 2 * (len(key) + 1)
5098                                 + entry_offset
5099                                 + string_struct.sizeof(),
5100                                 version_struct.OffsetToData,
5101                             )
5102 
5103                             ustr_offset = version_struct.OffsetToData + value_offset
5104                             try:
5105                                 value = self.get_string_u_at_rva(
5106                                     ustr_offset, max_length=string_struct.ValueLength
5107                                 )
5108                                 value_offset = self.get_offset_from_rva(ustr_offset)
5109                             except PEFormatError:
5110                                 self.__warnings.append(
5111                                     "Error parsing the version information, attempting "
5112                                     "to read StringTable Value string. Can't read "
5113                                     f"unicode string at offset 0x{ustr_offset:x}"
5114                                 )
5115                                 break
5116 
5117                             if string_struct.Length == 0:
5118                                 entry_offset = (
5119                                     stringtable_offset + stringtable_struct.Length
5120                                 )
5121                             else:
5122                                 entry_offset = self.dword_align(
5123                                     string_struct.Length + entry_offset,
5124                                     version_struct.OffsetToData,
5125                                 )
5126 
5127                             stringtable_struct.entries[key] = value
5128                             stringtable_struct.entries_offsets[key] = (
5129                                 key_offset,
5130                                 value_offset,
5131                             )
5132                             stringtable_struct.entries_lengths[key] = (
5133                                 len(key),
5134                                 len(value),
5135                             )
5136 
5137                         new_stringtable_offset = self.dword_align(
5138                             stringtable_struct.Length + stringtable_offset,
5139                             version_struct.OffsetToData,
5140                         )
5141 
5142                         # Check if the entry is crafted in a way that would lead
5143                         # to an infinite loop and break if so.
5144                         if new_stringtable_offset == stringtable_offset:
5145                             break
5146                         stringtable_offset = new_stringtable_offset
5147 
5148                         if stringtable_offset >= stringfileinfo_struct.Length:
5149                             break
5150 
5151             # Parse a VarFileInfo entry
5152             elif stringfileinfo_string and stringfileinfo_string.startswith(
5153                 b"VarFileInfo"
5154             ):
5155 
5156                 varfileinfo_struct = stringfileinfo_struct
5157                 varfileinfo_struct.name = "VarFileInfo"
5158 
5159                 if (
5160                     varfileinfo_struct.Type in (0, 1)
5161                     and varfileinfo_struct.ValueLength == 0
5162                 ):
5163 
5164                     var_offset = self.dword_align(
5165                         stringfileinfo_offset
5166                         + varfileinfo_struct.sizeof()
5167                         + 2 * (len(stringfileinfo_string) + 1),
5168                         version_struct.OffsetToData,
5169                     )
5170 
5171                     varfileinfo_struct.Var = []
5172 
5173                     # Process all entries
5174 
5175                     while True:
5176                         var_struct = self.__unpack_data__(
5177                             self.__Var_format__,
5178                             raw_data[var_offset:],
5179                             file_offset=start_offset + var_offset,
5180                         )
5181 
5182                         if not var_struct:
5183                             break
5184 
5185                         ustr_offset = (
5186                             version_struct.OffsetToData
5187                             + var_offset
5188                             + var_struct.sizeof()
5189                         )
5190                         try:
5191                             var_string = self.get_string_u_at_rva(ustr_offset)
5192                         except PEFormatError:
5193                             self.__warnings.append(
5194                                 "Error parsing the version information, "
5195                                 "attempting to read VarFileInfo Var string. "
5196                                 "Can't read unicode string at offset 0x{0:x}".format(
5197                                     ustr_offset
5198                                 )
5199                             )
5200                             break
5201 
5202                         if var_string is None:
5203                             break
5204 
5205                         varfileinfo_struct.Var.append(var_struct)
5206 
5207                         varword_offset = self.dword_align(
5208                             2 * (len(var_string) + 1)
5209                             + var_offset
5210                             + var_struct.sizeof(),
5211                             version_struct.OffsetToData,
5212                         )
5213                         orig_varword_offset = varword_offset
5214 
5215                         while (
5216                             varword_offset
5217                             < orig_varword_offset + var_struct.ValueLength
5218                         ):
5219                             word1 = self.get_word_from_data(
5220                                 raw_data[varword_offset : varword_offset + 2], 0
5221                             )
5222                             word2 = self.get_word_from_data(
5223                                 raw_data[varword_offset + 2 : varword_offset + 4], 0
5224                             )
5225                             varword_offset += 4
5226 
5227                             if isinstance(word1, int) and isinstance(word2, int):
5228                                 var_struct.entry = {
5229                                     var_string: "0x%04x 0x%04x" % (word1, word2)
5230                                 }
5231 
5232                         var_offset = self.dword_align(
5233                             var_offset + var_struct.Length, version_struct.OffsetToData
5234                         )
5235 
5236                         if var_offset <= var_offset + var_struct.Length:
5237                             break
5238 
5239             # Increment and align the offset
5240             stringfileinfo_offset = self.dword_align(
5241                 stringfileinfo_struct.Length + stringfileinfo_offset,
5242                 version_struct.OffsetToData,
5243             )
5244 
5245             # Check if all the StringFileInfo and VarFileInfo items have been processed
5246             if (
5247                 stringfileinfo_struct.Length == 0
5248                 or stringfileinfo_offset >= versioninfo_struct.Length
5249             ):
5250                 break
5251 
5252         self.FileInfo.append(finfo)
